3.Setup Manual (Recreation Guide)
Developer instructions for replicating this application in a new environment.
Step 1: Create Custom Table
Navigate to System Definition > Tables. Name it Network Database. Add fields for Request Number (String) and Work Status (Choice).
Step 2: Security Configuration (ACL)
Create a Write ACL on the Work Status field. Restrict access to the admin role and uncheck "Admin Overrides" if you want it locked for everyone during testing.
Step 3: Workflow Automation
Build the Flow in Workflow Studio. Ensure the Ask for Approval action is set to dotwalk to the Assignment Group.Manager.

4.QA Testing & Validation
Verified the request lifecycle through rigorous end-to-end testing.
•	Happy Path: Submitted request RITM0010013 was approved. Table status updated to 'Approved' and email sent.
•	Rejection Path: Manager rejected request; record status correctly flipped to 'Rejected'.
•	Access Control: Standard users received "Security Constraints" when attempting to bypass the workflow.



















